<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="V9" checkit-title="Homogeneous systems">
  <statement>
      <p>Consider the following homogeneous system of equations.</p>
      <me>\begin{matrix}
 -2 \, x_{1} &amp;  +  &amp; 6 \, x_{2} &amp;  -  &amp; 6 \, x_{3} &amp;  -  &amp; 2 \, x_{4} &amp;  +  &amp; 4 \, x_{5} &amp; = &amp; 0 \\
 3 \, x_{1} &amp;  -  &amp; 9 \, x_{2} &amp;  +  &amp; 9 \, x_{3} &amp;  +  &amp; x_{4} &amp;  &amp;  &amp; = &amp; 0 \\
 -3 \, x_{1} &amp;  +  &amp; 9 \, x_{2} &amp;  -  &amp; 9 \, x_{3} &amp;  -  &amp; 2 \, x_{4} &amp;  +  &amp; 3 \, x_{5} &amp; = &amp; 0 \\
 \end{matrix}</me>
    <ol>
        <li> Find the solution space of this system.</li>
        <li> Find a basis of the solution space.</li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
     <p><me>\mathrm{RREF}\,\left[\begin{array}{ccccc|c}
-2 &amp; 6 &amp; -6 &amp; -2 &amp; 4 &amp; 0 \\
3 &amp; -9 &amp; 9 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
-3 &amp; 9 &amp; -9 &amp; -2 &amp; 3 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{ccccc|c}
1 &amp; -3 &amp; 3 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]</me></p>
     <ol>
          <li>The solution space is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \, a - 3 \, b - c \\
a \\
b \\
3 \, c \\
c
\end{array}\right] \,\middle|\, a,b,c \in\mathbb R \right\} </m> </li>
          <li>A basis of the solution space is <m>\left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \\
1 \\
0 \\
0 \\
0
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-3 \\
0 \\
1 \\
0 \\
0
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-1 \\
0 \\
0 \\
3 \\
1
\end{array}\right] \right\}</m>.</li>
      </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>
